abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump will deliver his annual State of the Union speech on Feb. 4 after accepting an invitation from House Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Friday.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump will deliver his annual State of the Union speech on Feb. 4 after accepting an invitation from House Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump will deliver his annual State of the Union speech on Feb. 4 after accepting an invitation from House Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Friday.
headline_main: Trump to Deliver State of the Union Address on Feb. 4
headline_print_headline: Trump to Deliver State of the Union Address on Feb. 4

abstract: Cameroon's parliament granted special status on Friday to two English-speaking regions to try to calm a separatist insurgency that has killed 2,000 people, but the separatists said only independence would satisfy them.
snippet: Cameroon's parliament granted special status on Friday to two English-speaking regions to try to calm a separatist insurgency that has killed 2,000 people, but the separatists said only independence would satisfy them.
lead_paragraph: YAOUNDE — Cameroon's parliament granted special status on Friday to two English-speaking regions to try to calm a separatist insurgency that has killed 2,000 people, but the separatists said only independence would satisfy them.
headline_main: Cameroon Grants Special Status to Anglophone Regions
headline_print_headline: Cameroon Grants Special Status to Anglophone Regions

abstract: The International Criminal Court's chief prosecutor said on Friday she would launch a full investigation into alleged war crimes in the Palestinian Territories as soon as the court's jurisdiction had been established.
snippet: The International Criminal Court's chief prosecutor said on Friday she would launch a full investigation into alleged war crimes in the Palestinian Territories as soon as the court's jurisdiction had been established.
lead_paragraph: THE HAGUE — The International Criminal Court's chief prosecutor said on Friday she would launch a full investigation into alleged war crimes in the Palestinian Territories as soon as the court's jurisdiction had been established.
headline_main: ICC to Probe Alleged War Crimes in Palestinian Areas, Pending Jurisdiction
headline_print_headline: ICC to Probe Alleged War Crimes in Palestinian Areas, Pending Jurisdiction

abstract: Protests swept the globe in 2019, with millions of people taking to the streets from Catalonia to Colombia, Haiti to Hong Kong.

abstract: Pope Francis and U.N. Secretary-General Antonio Guterres on Friday appealed for nuclear disarmament, environmental protection and religious tolerance.

abstract: Dr. Moir’s radical and iconoclastic theories defied conventional views of the disease. But some scientists were ultimately won over.
snippet: Dr. Moir’s radical and iconoclastic theories defied conventional views of the disease. But some scientists were ultimately won over.
lead_paragraph: Robert D. Moir, a Harvard scientist whose radical theories of the brain plaques in Alzheimer’s defied conventional views of the disease, but whose research ultimately led to important proposals for how to treat it, died on Friday at a hospice in Milton, Mass. He was 58.

abstract: Donald Trump became the third president in U.S. history to be impeached when the House of Representatives formally charged him on Wednesday with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Donald Trump became the third president in U.S. history to be impeached when the House of Representatives formally charged him on Wednesday with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

abstract: The approval rating of Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro's government is dropping steadily and its negative rating is climbing, a CNI/Ibope poll showed on Friday, as his combative political style and a weak recovery weigh on his popularity.
snippet: The approval rating of Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro's government is dropping steadily and its negative rating is climbing, a CNI/Ibope poll showed on Friday, as his combative political style and a weak recovery weigh on his popularity.
lead_paragraph: BRASILIA — The approval rating of Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro's government is dropping steadily and its negative rating is climbing, a CNI/Ibope poll showed on Friday, as his combative political style and a weak recovery weigh on his popularity.
headline_main: Brazil Poll Shows Rising Rejection of Bolsonaro
headline_print_headline: Brazil Poll Shows Rising Rejection of Bolsonaro

abstract: A St. Louis-area man who is charged in the death of his girlfriend's 8-month-old son repeatedly abused the child and bit off his nipples, authorities say.

abstract: Greece will extradite a Russian man suspected of having laundered billions of dollars in the digital currency bitcoin to France, the justice minister decided on Friday, court officials said.
snippet: Greece will extradite a Russian man suspected of having laundered billions of dollars in the digital currency bitcoin to France, the justice minister decided on Friday, court officials said.
lead_paragraph: ATHENS — Greece will extradite a Russian man suspected of having laundered billions of dollars in the digital currency bitcoin to France, the justice minister decided on Friday, court officials said.
